# Agent workflow (LLM only)

Meta-repo at `mails.com/`. Child folders are **separate git repos**. Execute tasks yourself; do not instruct the user to run commands you can run.

## Topology

```
mails.com/          → mails-com/workspace   (docs/orchestration; this repo)
mails-backend/      → mails-com/back      :3000  Fly.io
mails-frontend/     → mails-com/front     :3001  Cloudflare Workers
```

- Meta-repo `.gitignore` excludes child folders — never `git add mails-backend/` or `mails-frontend/` from root.
- Git commit/push happens **inside each child repo**, not from workspace root.

## Before editing

| Scope | Read |
| --- | --- |
| Both stacks | `.cursor/rules/stack.mdc` |
| Backend detail | `mails-backend/.cursor/rules/project-stack.mdc` |
| Frontend detail | `mails-frontend/CONTRIBUTING.md` |
| API | Backend README auth section + `mails-frontend/src/lib/api.ts` |

Cross-stack: trace **DB migration → sqlc query → handler → `UserJSON` + `contracts/*.json` → `src/lib/schemas` + `api.ts` → UI** before coding.

## API contracts (JSON shape sync)

`back` and `front` are separate repos — contract files are **duplicated** (same bytes in each). CI tests keep backend `UserJSON` and frontend Zod in sync with `contracts/user.json`.

**When you change the user API shape (`GET/PATCH /api/me`):**

1. Update `UserJSON` + `newUserJSON` in `mails-backend/internal/handler/response.go`
2. Update `mails-backend/contracts/user.json`
3. From workspace root: `make sync-contracts` (copies user contract to frontend)
4. Update `mails-frontend/src/lib/schemas/user.ts` (Zod `userSchema`)
5. Commit **both child repos** (`back` first, then `front`)
6. Verify: `go test ./...` + `golangci-lint run` in backend; `npm run validate` in frontend

Runtime: `api.me()` / `api.updateMe()` parse responses with `userSchema.strict()` — extra or missing fields throw immediately in the browser.

Future list resources (`Session`, `ConnectedAccount`): same pattern — add `contracts/{name}.json`, mapper tests, Zod schema, extend `api:validate`.

## Task order

1. Read rules + grep existing implementations.
2. Split changes: `mails-backend` vs `mails-frontend`.
3. **Backend first** if: migration, API route/body, auth, session, CORS.
4. **Frontend only** if: UI/i18n with no API change.
5. Verify each repo (commands below).
6. Commit per repo (only when user asks).
7. Push per repo (only when user asks). If API/migration changed: **push `back` before `front`**.

## Backend verify (`mails-backend/`)

After changing `internal/db/queries/*.sql`:

```bash
sqlc generate
go test ./...
go build -o /tmp/mails-api-test ./cmd/api
go vet ./...
golangci-lint run
```

- `internal/db/generated/` is gitignored — CI fails if you skip `sqlc generate`.
- Schema: goose file `internal/db/migrations/NNNN_desc.sql` with Up/Down. Dev auto-migrates on `air`; prod migrates via Fly `release_command ./api migrate`.

## Frontend verify (`mails-frontend/`)

```bash
npm run validate
```

Equals CI: format + lint + i18n + seo + **api contracts** + typecheck + test + build.

- Locales: always update `public/locales/en/` and `public/locales/es/` together.
- Use static `t('key')` — no dynamic keys (i18n-check).
- i18n + react-hook-form: Zod messages must refresh on language change — use `schemaRef` + re-`trigger()` (see `src/pages/settings-page.tsx`).

## Local smoke (workspace root)

```bash
make dev            # Overmind: backend :3000 + frontend :3001
make stop           # stop both
make sync-contracts # copy mails-backend/contracts/*.json → mails-frontend/contracts/
```

- `make dev` without `-N` → Overmind sets `PORT=5000` on first process; overrides `.env` `PORT=3000`; conflicts with macOS AirPlay.
- Health: `curl localhost:3000/ping`, `curl localhost:3000/health`
- Login: `window.location` to `/auth/google` — not `fetch`. API calls: `credentials: "include"`.

## Commits (one repo per commit)

Only when user explicitly requests. Never `--no-verify` unless user says so.

**Backend** (`cd mails-backend`):

```bash
git add <paths>
git commit -m "feat(scope): description"
```

Lefthook: gofumpt, goimports, golangci-lint --fix, go mod tidy. commit-msg: `feat|fix|chore|docs|refactor|test|ci|perf`.

**Frontend** (`cd mails-frontend`):

```bash
git add <paths>
git commit -m "feat(scope): description"
```

Husky lint-staged + commitlint: `feat|fix|docs|style|refactor|perf|test|build|ci|chore|revert`.

Never commit `.env`, `.env.local`, or secrets.

## Push

```bash
cd mails-backend && git push origin main
cd mails-frontend && git push origin main
```

- `back` push → CI → Fly deploy + goose migrate.
- `front` push → CI → Cloudflare build (`VITE_*` are build-time).

## API quick reference

- Errors: `{"error":"snake_code","message":"human"}`
- User: `{id,email,name,avatar_url,role,locale,theme}` — flat, no `data` envelope; canonical contract in `contracts/user.json` (both repos)
- Partial update: `PATCH /api/me` with any of `name`, `locale`, `theme` (at least one field)
- No `PATCH /api/me/locale` — removed; use unified `PATCH /api/me`

## Do not

- Commit child code from meta-repo git
- Skip `sqlc generate` after SQL query edits
- Push frontend before backend when migration/API changed
- Create commits/pushes without user request
- Edit `.cursor/plans/*.plan.md` when user says not to
